Newly remodeled and worth sitting with your coffee and gluten-free pastry!  Too many tasty options.  A place where I can eat most of the items on the menu but have to rein myself in. Patty and the team are terrific. I only wish they opened earlier!
This place is amazing! As a celiac, there are only so many places that you can feel comfortable eating and of those, only some are good. The bread and sweets here are amazing. Love this place!

This is really for their presence at the California Ave Farmers Market on Sundays in Palo Alto. I've tried their mock rye bread, baguette, buns (perfect for burgers), and cinnamon rolls.  They are all so good--and it's such a treat to have someone else do the baking. :)
People don't make gluten-free bread like this.  Twelve years of a celiac life and their focaccia bread is the first thing to ever get bread's texture right.  Desserts. Yes.
